<br>
There are fewer and fewer places in this game where you can take a full group to for a full night of xp. It is still my contention that for the time put in, chardok is still the best xp bang for your buck in this game.<br>
<br>
If you want to solo, go to a zone that is set-up for that.  I am sure that you can find things to solo in Skyfire, Burning woods - hell even DL has a few blue mobs to a level 58.  The point is you can solo anywhere - but group xp is getting worse and worse these days and the choices are getting slim.  Chardok is one of them, and I personally think it's pretty greedy on someone's part to ask an entire group to give up a camp just so you can kill a handful of mobs.<br>
